Existing Infrastructure
Cost-Efficient: Utilizes already invested resources.
Faster Setup: Immediate availability.
Proven Stability: Known stability and performance.
Scalability Limits: May not scale with future growth.
Technical Debt: Inherited legacy issues.
Limited Flexibility: May restrict innovation.


Creating New Infrastructure
Customization: Made to fit your exact needs.
Scalability: Designed to grow with the business.
Modern Tools: Leverage the latest technology.
Cost: High initial investment.
Setup Time: Requires significant time and resources to build.
Risk: Unproven stability.
